{
  "stem": "24515.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, I knew my father wouldn't come alone.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, after that, you see, pretty soon, then, war broke out, and of course, all visas were cancelled.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The English visas were no good.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We got in this situation, where the Dutch wouldn't let you in [? as ?] the British said they would.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the British would say, you can come if you went to Holland, and this catch-22 killed more people than you can shake a stick at.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Nevertheless-- that's another very long story, [INAUDIBLE] Germany.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Nevertheless, I somehow managed to get [? another ?] Secretary of State to say he would sign admission, if the Refugee Committee would ask for it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I didn't think for a moment that the Refugee Committee could mess this one up, but, of course, a week later, I got a letter-- phone call from the man, who had helped me, marvelous chap, that the-- the answer was, no.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I know now that they tried everything they possibly could to get out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I have the passport, if you want to see it, has visa for Haiti, for Panama, for Shanghai, and if they wanted to other places-- England, of course, as I just mentioned.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They didn't make it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we wrote by Red Cross letters.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "OK?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was afraid to write too much to my mother or father, to make-- make the Germans, see, they got sons in England.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we wrote a few and they wrote a few.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- so we found out the father was, had been dead.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the next thing we knew, or one of the next things we knew, was this famous death certificate from the [INAUDIBLE], which is the registry of Dachau.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my uncle, who was in London, knew about it.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
